data.description: Space, light, luxury. Built in 1907, this attached brick property consists of 5 bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms across 3 upper levels and a fully finished basement, and has been lovingly expanded and updated throughout. High ceilings and charming exposed brick walls in living & dining rooms. Stunning gourmet kitchen with stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, tile flooring and access to the outdoor tiled private rear patio. Spacious finished basement with large rec space, two storage closets, furnace-hot water heater room, laundry and 1/2 bathroom with gated access to street and patio. 2nd level consists of two bedrooms, plus a luxurious spa-like bath with jacuzzi tub - enjoy a soak then unwind outside with direct access to a lovely rear porch. 3rd level encompasses 2 large bedrooms, a full bathroom and access to an outdoor balcony with a spiral staircase to the fantastic roof deck providing great city views and the perfect spot for relaxation and entertaining. Revitalized Columbia Heights is among Washington’s most diverse neighborhoods and features plenty of good eats ranging from Cuban to Dominican to Vietnamese. Close to Giant, Yes Market, Trader Joe’s and the brand new Lidl. Surrounded by historic architecture, close to the Columbia Heights Metro, Target and the Tivoli Theatre, home of the Gala Hispanic Theater. Nearby bars and cafes include Taqueria Habanero, Bad Saint, Wonderland and Thip Kao. Enjoy your downtime at nearby Bruce Monroe Community Park - tennis, basketball and community gardening. Welcome home!
